
| # | Attribute        | Range (−1 to +1)                 | Applies to…                                |
| - | ---------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| 1 | **Morality**     | Evil ↔ Good                      | Characters, motives, outcomes              |
| 2 | **Wealth/Value** | Cheap/Low ↔ Rich/High            | Objects, stakes, worlds                    |
| 3 | **Mood**         | Sad ↔ Happy                      | Emotional tone of scene, resolution, world |
| 4 | **World Nature** | Realistic/Tech ↔ Magical/Fantasy | Setting, logic, rules                      |
| 5 | **Energy**       | Passive ↔ Active                 | Characters, events, actions                |
| 6 | **Stability** 🆕 | Chaotic ↔ Orderly                | Worlds, systems, scenes, climaxes          |
| 7 | **Control** 🆕   | Imposed/Forced ↔ Chosen/Freedom  | Motivation, actions, conflicts             |


| Attribute (Label)          | Matches Pool Category | Reasoning/Notes                              |
| -------------------------- | --------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| **A: Morality**            | Characters            | Defines role in conflict (hero/villain etc.) |
| **B: Wealth / Value**      | Objects / MacGuffins  | Objects are tied to desire, value            |
| **C: Emotion / Mood**      | Tone / Theme          | Emotional color of the story                 |
| **D: Worldbuilding**       | Settings              | Sets genre, time, place, logic               |
| **E: Action / Energy**     | Actions / Events      | Dictates story movement / tension            |
| **F: Perspective / Theme** | Obstacles / Hurdles   | Challenges the worldview or goal             |
| **G: Story Beat**          | Events / Resolution   | Drives story structure, turning points       |

| Category             | # Pools | Avg. Items/Pool | Total Items | Notes                                  |
| -------------------- | ------- | --------------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------- |
| **Characters**       | 5       | 5–10            | \~40        | Keep emotional depth and recognition   |
| **Motives / Goals**  | 5       | 6–12            | \~60        | Low volume, high clarity               |
| **Settings**         | 7       | 20–30           | \~180       | Rich variety, low emotional attachment |
| **Obstacles**        | 6       | 15–25           | \~150       | High variety, reusability              |
| **Story Beats**      | 5       | 10–15           | \~75        | Memorable narrative structure          |
| **Resolutions**      | 4       | 6–10            | \~35        | Strong payoff moments                  |
| **Objects/Triggers** | 3       | 20–30           | \~75        | Sound, PNG, abstract usable things     |

Attribute	Times used	Slots used
A-F	5 times	6 × 5 = 30 slots
G	6 times	1 × 6 = 6 slots
Total		30 + 6 = 36 slots



Start	2–3	Villain: Demon, Robber; Hero, Heroine	Simple, iconic, archetypal
Mid-game	4–6	Add Mentor, Sidekick, Rival	Adds complexity, subplots
Late-game	7+	Factions, new heroes/villains	Full story ecosystem

maybe we can do kind of reorder.. like [a.x a.y a.z ] compared to [b.x, by, bz] , [b.y, b.z. bx] , permutation maybe 3! or 3^3

Compute dot products 𝑑𝑝 = 𝐴⃗⋅𝑝 (𝐵⃗) for each permutation.

So now let’s build your 12-neuron setup, where:

You have 7 attributes:
Let’s call them:
A: Morality
B: Wealth
C: Mood
D: Worldbuilding
E: Energy
F: Perspective/Theme
G: Story Beat ← this one will appear 6 times

✅ Attribute distribution:
Attribute	Desired Count
A–F	5 each
G	6
Total	36 slots